
[1]ecclesiastical

   ECCLESIAS'TICAL, . [L; Gr.an assembly or meeting, whence a church; to
   call forth or convoke; to call.]

   Pertaining or relating to the church; as ecclesiastical discipline or
   government; ecclesiastical affairs, history or policy; ecclesiastical
   courts.

   Ecclesiastical State is the body of the clergy.
